The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 25: The department of telecom (DoT) has directed all service providers to comply with the regulations on pesky calls and discontinue the phone connections of non-registered tele-marketing companies by October 19. All licencees are required to ensure that the directive is complied with, a DoT letter said.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 25: Market regulator Sebi has extended the alternate method of payment to new rights issues such as Tata Motors Ltd and Sadhna Nitro Chem on a pilot basis. In the alternative method, investors will not have to pay money till the final allotment.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 25: The government has extended incentives to automobile sector by adding cars and two-wheelers of certain specifications under the market-linked focus products category to boost export.                             
	 Calcutta, Sept. 25 : An indefinite strike in the states jute industry is imminent following the deadlock of the tripartite meeting held by the labour commissioner today.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 25: The government has reconstituted the central direct taxes advisory committee for 2008-2010 to suggest measures for removing administrative and procedural roadblocks.                                                                                                                         
